Drones are increasingly used in applications such as last-mile delivery and infrastructure inspection, but their safe operation, especially in high-speed scenarios, remains a critical challenge. Existing vision- and LiDAR-based obstacle localization methods suffer from motion blur, latency, and low spatio-temporal resolution, making them inadequate for detecting and tracking fast-moving objects. In this work, we present HawkEye, a drone obstacle avoidance system that fuses event cameras and LiDAR to achieve high-frequency, accurate 3D tracking of dynamic objects. By leveraging the complementary strengths of both sensors, Hawkeye enables robust real-time sensing and safe evasive maneuvers, addressing a key requirement for the large-scale deployment of autonomous drones. Demo: https://wenhua00.github.io/HawkEye/.